Creating a custom Terraform module for an AWS API Gateway REST API involves encapsulating the configuration and resources needed to create and manage the API Gateway REST API in a reusable and modular way. Below is an example of how you can structure such a Terraform module:

hcl
Copy code
# Directory structure
terraform-aws-api-gateway/
├── main.tf
├── variables.tf
├── outputs.tf
└── README.md
main.tf: This file contains the main configuration for the AWS API Gateway REST API. It defines the resources such as aws_api_gateway_rest_api, aws_api_gateway_resource, aws_api_gateway_method, etc.
variables.tf: This file defines input variables that can be customized when using the module. Variables like name, description, tags, etc., can be defined here.
outputs.tf: This file defines output values that can be useful when consuming the module. For example, the API Gateway endpoint URL can be an output.
README.md: This file contains documentation on how to use the module, what variables are available, and any other relevant information.
Here's a basic example of what these files might contain:

main.tf:

hcl
Copy code
provider "aws" {
  region = var.region
}

resource "aws_api_gateway_rest_api" "api" {
  name        = var.name
  description = var.description
}

resource "aws_api_gateway_resource" "resource" {
  rest_api_id = aws_api_gateway_rest_api.api.id
  parent_id   = aws_api_gateway_rest_api.api.root_resource_id
  path_part   = var.path_part
}

resource "aws_api_gateway_method" "method" {
  rest_api_id   = aws_api_gateway_rest_api.api.id
  resource_id   = aws_api_gateway_resource.resource.id
  http_method   = var.http_method
  authorization = var.authorization
}

# Other resources like aws_api_gateway_integration, aws_api_gateway_deployment, etc., can be added as needed.
variables.tf:

hcl
Copy code
variable "name" {
  description = "The name of the API Gateway REST API"
}

variable "description" {
  description = "The description of the API Gateway REST API"
}

variable "path_part" {
  description = "The path part for the resource"
}

variable "http_method" {
  description = "The HTTP method for the API Gateway method"
}

variable "authorization" {
  description = "The authorization type for the API Gateway method"
  default     = "NONE"  # Default to no authorization
}

variable "region" {
  description = "The AWS region"
}
outputs.tf:

hcl
Copy code
output "api_endpoint" {
  description = "The URL of the API Gateway REST API"
  value       = aws_api_gateway_rest_api.api.invoke_url
}
README.md:

markdown
Copy code
# AWS API Gateway Terraform Module

This module creates an AWS API Gateway REST API.

## Usage

```hcl
module "api_gateway" {
  source      = "path/to/module"
  name        = "MyAPI"
  description = "My API Gateway REST API"
  path_part   = "myresource"
  http_method = "GET"
  region      = "us-east-1"
}
Variables
name: The name of the API Gateway REST API.
description: The description of the API Gateway REST API.
path_part: The path part for the resource.
http_method: The HTTP method for the API Gateway method.
authorization: The authorization type for the API Gateway method.
region: The AWS region.
Outputs
api_endpoint: The URL of the API Gateway REST API.
css
Copy code

This structure provides a reusable module that can be easily customize
